---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import profilePicture from "../assets/profile-picture.jpg";
---

<div id="container">
  <section
    class="relative py-8 sm:py-12 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800"
    aria-label="Introduction"
  >
    <section
      class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 justify-center lg:justify-items-end py-8 sm:py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-24 mx-0 sm:mx-4 lg:mx-8"
    >
      <div
        class="order-2 lg:order-1 p-2 sm:p-4 justify-self-center lg:justify-self-end space-y-6"
      >
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h1
            class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl dark:text-gray-200 leading-normal"
          >
            Hi, I&apos;m{" "}
            <span class="text-(--theme-5) font-bold">Josh</span> ðŸ‘‹
          </h1>
        </div>

        <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-4">
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            I build software with <strong>TypeScript</strong>, <strong
              >Go</strong
            >, and <strong>Python</strong>, everything from AI-powered yoga
            instructors to hackathon-winning platforms.
          </p>

          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            I'm a Full Stack Engineer at <a
              href="https://www.letsdothis.com/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-(--theme-5) hover:underline font-semibold"
              >Let&apos;s Do This</a
            >, where I build event discovery and booking platforms. We handle
            some of the biggest events in the world, including the London
            Marathon ballot system. I work with <strong>TypeScript</strong>, <strong
              >Node.js</strong
            > and <strong>Next.js</strong>, and on systems that process hundreds
            of thousands of registrations.
          </p>

          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Right now I'm exploring everything from AI agents to low-level
            systems work - basically whatever seems interesting. I write about
            the problems I run into on my <a
              class="text-(--theme-5) hover:underline font-semibold"
              href="/blog">blog</a
            >.
          </p>

          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Before this, I spent a decade selling enterprise software. It made
            me the kind of engineer who cares more about solving real problems
            than writing clever code.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 pt-4">
            <a
              href="#projects"
              class="flex-1 sm:flex-none inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 sm:py-3 text-sm sm:text-base font-medium text-white bg-(--theme-5) rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
            >
              Projects
            </a>
            <a
              href="/blog"
              class="flex-1 sm:flex-none inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 sm:py-3 text-sm sm:text-base font-medium text-white bg-(--theme-5) rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
            >
              Blog
            </a>
            <a
              href="#contact"
              class="flex-1 sm:flex-none inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 sm:py-3 text-sm sm:text-base font-medium text-white bg-(--theme-5) rounded-md hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
            >
              Contact
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="order-1 lg:order-2 flex justify-center items-start">
        <div
          class="w-48 h-48 sm:w-64 sm:h-64 md:w-80 md:h-80 lg:w-[400px] lg:h-[400px] shrink-0"
        >
          <Image
            src={profilePicture}
            alt="Josh Tuddenham"
            width={400}
            height={400}
            loading="eager"
            fetchpriority="high"
            class="w-full h-full rounded-full border-4 border-(--theme-5) cursor-pointer dark:brightness-90 object-cover"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</div>
